The shrill ring of the phone ripped me from my sleep. I stumbled into the living room to answer it, but as I reached for the receiver, I noticed the time. It was 2:00 AM. I shook off the shock and pressed the talk button. “Hello?” “Dong Jin, it’s Grandma.” Her voice was soft and timid. “Grandma, is everything okay?” I asked. “I’m fine. I just wanted to tell you that I’m sorry for all the pain I caused you.” “Grandma, what are you talking about?” I asked, my heart pounding in my chest. “I just wanted to apologize. I hope you can forgive me.” I was shocked. My grandmother had never apologized for anything in her life. “Grandma, you don’t have to apologize.” I said, confused. “I just wanted to say that I’m sorry. I love you.” “I love you too, Grandma.” I hung up the phone and headed back to bed. I lay there for a while, unable to fall asleep. After a while, I sat up and reached for the phone. I picked it up and dialed her number. The phone rang, and then I heard her voice. “Hello?” “Grandma, it’s me,” I said. “I’m sorry, I was asleep.” “It’s okay. I just wanted to say that I’m sorry.” “Grandma, it’s okay. I’m just glad that you’re doing better.” “Thank you, Dong Jin. I love you.” “I love you too, Grand
